        <p><b>Pollution:</b> Though it can also fall onto the environment pillar, the pollution
            that is
            discussed
            here
            is not targeted at the environment but
            at us instead, laws and legislations with the goal of protecting our health as well
            as prevent
            certain
            activities done by businesses and other organizations.</p>
        <p><b>Human rights:</b> These are moral principles or norms that describe certain
            standards of how
            an
            individual should behave, these are regularly protected as natural and legal
            rights both nationaly and internationally. They are commonly understood as something
            that is
            inherent in
            us
            no matter the race, age or gender.
        <p>Though too broad a subject, a very small part of it does belong to the objective of
            social
            sustainability, of how we should treat both ourselves and the environment...</p>
